    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Culture at Chiripa dating from 1000-800 BCE, based on calibrated radiocarbon dates from 1992 and 1996 excavations. This phase is marked by a growth in population and an early example of communal architecture in the Lake Titicaca Basin, a semi-subterranean plaza or court.</Note_Text>
